On the Eve of the CCP’s Fourth Plenum, the Spotlight Unexpectedly Shifts to Sydney, Australia.
 A luxury-car DUI case has ignited global attention among Chinese communities. At her third court appearance, Yang Lanlan’s lawyer confirmed they are “engaged in plea negotiations” with prosecutors—timed precisely before the Fourth Plenum. Public opinion suspects this seemingly ordinary car crash is being pushed onto Zhongnanhai’s battlefield of narrative warfare. Who is she? Why so sensitive? The truth is fermenting. author: China Insights
description:
Just as the countdown to the CCP’s Fourth Plenum begins, Trump has officially announced: the U.S.–China trade war is back on! U.S. Treasury Secretary Bessent and Trade Representative Greer appeared side by side in a rare joint rebuke of Beijing, accusing the CCP of weaponizing rare earths to conduct “economic coercion” against the world. The United States, together with the EU, Japan, Australia, India, and other partners—seven countries in all—has launched an “Anti–Rare Earths Blockade Alliance” and is rebuilding supply chains.

description:
On the eve of the CCP’s Fourth Plenum, Beijing has descended into chaos. He Weidong has vanished for seven months, Zhang Shengmin has taken over, Xi Yuanping has made a high-profile appearance in Gansu—the undercurrents of power in the military are surging. At the same time, the dirge “Good-for-Nothing” is sweeping the internet, CCTV has suffered a public fiasco, and a new wave of intellectual awakening is rising—China’s ruling party is facing an unprecedented political shock.
